This species was recently described and illustrated (
Moctezuma et al . 2019
). To the original description of the female we add: cephalic trituberculate carina of head with carinate central tubercle, anteriorly more projected not as raised as lateral, conical tubercles; frons with superficially impressed punctures; pronotal sculpture completely smooth with superficially impressed punctures; pronotal process trituberculate
